  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0da2\u0db6 \u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db4\u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dcf\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dbb\u0d82\u0da2\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ranjan for the first vacancy in the Sahab national list",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Opposition leader Sajith Premadasa said in Colombo today (26) that former Member of Parliament Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake will be appointed for the first vacancy in the national list of Samagi Jana Balavega.",
        "The opposition leader also mentioned that Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake will be invited to act as the head of the country's corruption prevention program.",
        "Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake is entitled to partial freedom and should be given full freedom to engage in politics full time, he said this while attending a joint press conference with former Minister of State Ranjan Ramanayake who was pardoned by the President at the office of the opposition leader in Marx Fernando Mawatha, Colombo.",
        "The opposition leader also said that he is extremely happy about the freedom that Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake, who was a people's leader who fought against fraud and corruption, got."
      ],
